This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition and natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with audio data. Additionally, it involves machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses practical training and decoding issues, which could fall under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
